Chinese artist Ai Weiwei aims to
take up a guest professorship in Berlin, the  Bild Zeitung 
reported, without saying where it got the information or how or
when he will assume the post.  Weiwei, a human-rights activist, was released from jail in
 China  in June but must remain in Beijing for a year, according
to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
